description:
&lt;p&gt;The Medical Records Department is responsible for the management, storage and provision of records for all outpatient clinics and admitted patients at our Winchester Hospital.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The Department is currently looking to recruit enthusiastic Bank Medical Records Clerks to work ideally full time 37.5 hours per week (Mon to Fri) or part time 22.5.hrs or 3 full days per week in long term Temporary assignments. No experience necessary for the right person.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be part of a friendly team that retrieve and return patient notes throughout the hospital and ensure that they are tracked and monitored correctly throughout the Trust’s hospital sites. Therefore, you must be accurate, organised and possess excellent communication skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The work can sometimes be physically demanding. Some records can be very heavy, and they need to be lifted, carried and transported on foot constantly throughout the day.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact Janice Johnson on 01256 313374 or email janice.johnson@hhft.nhs.uk.&lt;/p&gt;
